title: Funky ST Machine
info:
This is my second song for ATARI STe.
It's 8-channels digital music (min. 1Mb RAM to load/play).
Recorded from real hardware (ATARI 1040 STe 4Mb) with 50kHz quality.
Radical STe stereo replaced by 60-40/40-60. *NO* further mastering.

Made in 10.2011 for Silly Venture 2011 multichannel digital music compo. [3rd place]

Hardware used while composing:
- Atari 520ST 4Mb + HxC USB (must work also on 1Mb)
- Atari 1040STe 4Mb + satan-disk 2Gb (must work also on 1Mb, then probably from FDD only)
- Yamaha E423 synthesizer
- tested on Falcon 030 14Mb with 4Gb CF card (must work also on 4Mb)

Software used:
- Hex-Tracker v0.843
- Octalyser v0.96
- tested and recorded from MOD-PLAYER 1.0 by Christian Dahl (50kHz sound-quality).

Respect to software makers: Paulo Simoes, The Black Lotus, New Core, Reward, Christian Dahl.
Greetz to 505 and YM-Rockerz.
